                "invention-title": [
                    "Glass hydrogen-doped combustion device",
                    "一种玻璃掺氢燃烧装置"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of float glass manufacturing equipment, in particular to a glass hydrogen-doped combustion device which comprises an oxygen-fuel combustion spray gun suitable for adopting fuel with the hydrogen volume proportion of 60%-70% for combustion; and the heat storage combustion area is installed on the downstream of the total oxygen combustion spray gun, a plurality of sets of oxygen combustion spray guns are sequentially installed in the heat storage combustion area, and the oxygen combustion spray guns are suitable for adopting fuel with the hydrogen volume proportion not larger than 60% for combustion. Fuel storage equipment needs to be arranged in the heat storage combustion area, so that fuel with a low hydrogen proportion is adopted, and the defect of hydrogen embrittlement of equipment in the glass hydrogen-doped combustion device caused by hydrogen is overcome. According to the hydrogen-doped glass combustion device, the fuel doped with hydrogen is used as a combustion substance, and the optimal design of the oxygen-fuel combustion spray gun and the oxygen combustion spray gun is combined, so that more expensive hydrogen storage equipment does not need to be replaced while carbon dioxide emission is reduced, and the production cost of producing by taking hydrogen as the glass combustion fuel is reduced."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及浮法玻璃制造设备技术领域，具体涉及一种玻璃掺氢燃烧装置，包括：全氧燃烧喷枪，其适于采用氢气体积比例为60％－70％的燃料进行燃烧；蓄热燃烧区，安装在全氧燃烧喷枪下游，蓄热燃烧区内依次安装有多组氧气燃烧喷枪，氧气燃烧喷枪适于采用氢气体积比例不大于60％的燃料进行燃烧。在蓄热燃烧区需要配置燃料储存设备，故采用氢气比例较低的燃料，防止氢气对玻璃掺氢燃烧装置中的设备造成氢脆缺陷。玻璃掺氢燃烧装置通过使用掺有氢气的燃料作为燃烧物质，并结合全氧燃烧喷枪和氧气燃烧喷枪的优化设计，能够减少二氧化碳排放的同时无需更换更加昂贵的储氢设备，降低了将氢气作为玻璃燃烧燃料进行生产的生产成本。"
                }
